name: 3-(3,4-dimethoxyphenyl)propionic acid

The net effect of each methoxy group might be around +10°C. - The propyl chain (–CH2–CH2–CH2–) connected to the phenyl ring will likely have a mild effect on the melting point. Such alkyl chains can increase the melting point due to increased van der Waals interactions, possibly by +5°C. Considering these functional group contributions, we can estimate the melting point of the target compound.
